          <h3>Submission Guidelines</h3>
          <p>
            Research from any discipline (natural sciences, social sciences, humanities, etc.) is eligible for publication
            in the Maryland Undergraduate Research Journal (MURJ).
          </p>
          <br>
          <h3>Eligibility</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Primary author must be a University of Maryland undergraduate, or a recent graduate (â‰¤1 year) of the
              University of Maryland.
            </li>
            <li>
              Submissions must contain original research conducted by a University of Maryland undergraduate.
            </li>
            <li>
              Submissions may not have been previously published in another research journal.
            </li>
            <li>
              Submissions must be approved for publication in MURJ by a mentor (principal investigator, faculty
              member, etc.).
            </li>
            <li>
              Mentors may be listed as secondary authors.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <br>
          <h3>Formatting</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Submissions should fall within 2,000 to 4,000 words in length; submissions that fall outside this range
              will also be considered.
            </li>
            <li>
              Any relevant figures/tables should be included in the submission, and labeled appropriately. </li>
            <li>
              Submissions should be a single file; separate attachments will not be considered without prior approval. 
            </li>
            <li>
              Submissions must be in one of the following file formats: DOC, DOCX.
            </li>
            <li>
              Successful submissions will be formatted by MURJ prior to publication.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <br>
          <h3>Structure</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Submissions do not need to follow any particular structure; however, submissions should be structured
              similarly to other research articles.
            </li>
            <li>
              Submissions should include an abstract as a brief summary; abstracts will not be included in the word count. 
            <li>
              Submissions should follow APA style for any references, citations, etc.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <br>
          <h3>Submission Deadline</h3>
          <p>
            MURJ has no submission deadline; submissions are accepted on a rolling basis.
          </p>
          <br>
          <h3>Questions?</h3>
          <p>
            If you have questions about any of the above Submission Guidelines, please email us at <a style="text-decoration: underline" href="mailto: umd.murj@gmail.com" target="_blank">umd.murj@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
